10:54.120 --> 11:03.329 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
road of people who appear
middle-class, but
are on the edge of financial
ruin; and much

11:03.429 --> 11:07.600 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
more.

11:07.700 --> 11:15.475 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president-elect moved a bit
closer to
getting his Cabinet in place
with another

11:15.575 --> 11:18.011 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
round of confirmation hearings
today.

11:18.111 --> 11:23.182 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The most contentious was for his
treasury
secretary pick, Steven Mnuchin,
a billionaire

11:23.283 --> 11:27.153 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
banker who worked at Goldman
Sachs and owned
a hedge fund.

11:27.253 --> 11:30.490 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There was important news that
came out during
the hearing.

11:30.590 --> 11:35.695 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mnuchin said that he would
support raising
the debt ceiling sooner rather
than later,

11:35.795 --> 11:38.031 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and not risk the country
defaulting.

11:38.131 --> 11:42.569 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The president-elect had
previously suggested
that he might want to
renegotiate the government's

11:42.669 --> 11:44.637 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
obligations instead.

11:44.737 --> 11:49.375 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But most of the focus was on
Mnuchin's business
background and investments.

11:49.475 --> 11:51.477 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Lisa Desjardins has our report.

11:51.578 --> 11:55.582 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: He came
prepared for a broadside
attack.

11:55.682 --> 11:59.052 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
STEVEN MNUCHIN, Treasury
Secretary Nominee:
I have been maligned as taking
advantage of

11:59.152 --> 12:03.056 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
others' hardships in order to
earn a buck.

12:03.156 --> 12:06.259 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Nothing could be further than
the truth.

12:06.359 --> 12:10.830 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Steven Mnuchin
began his
appeal to become treasury
secretary by defending

12:10.930 --> 12:16.336 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
his record at the helm of
OneWest, a bank
that Democratic critics say was
a foreclosure

12:16.436 --> 12:18.171 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
machine during the housing
crisis.

12:18.271 --> 12:23.910 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVEN MNUCHIN: OneWest extended
over 100,000
loan modifications to delinquent
borrowers

12:24.010 --> 12:26.245 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to try to help them out of a bad
situation.

12:26.346 --> 12:30.883 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But Oregon
Democrat Ron Wyden
disputed Mnuchin's version.

12:30.984 --> 12:32.752 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

12:32.852 --> 12:36.155 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
RON WYDEN (D), Oregon:
Investigations found
that the bank frequently
mishandled documents

12:36.255 --> 12:38.791 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and skipped over reviewing them.

12:38.891 --> 12:48.134 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
All it took to plunge families
into the nightmare
of potentially losing their home
was 30 seconds

12:48.234 --> 12:52.305 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of sloppy paperwork and a few
haphazard signatures.

12:52.405 --> 12:57.510 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: It was some of
the most dogged
questioning of president-elect
Trump's nominees

12:57.610 --> 13:00.713 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
yet, and it was tense between
senators.

13:00.813 --> 13:02.548 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

13:02.649 --> 13:07.720 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAT ROBERTS (R), Kansas: Senator
Wyden, I
have got a Valium pill you might
want to take

13:07.820 --> 13:08.755 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
before the second round,

13:08.855 --> 13:10.690 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

13:10.790 --> 13:13.026 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHERROD BROWN (D), Ohio: Mr.
Chairman, Mr.
Chairman, I hope that that
comment about Valium

13:13.126 --> 13:17.296 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
doesn't set the tone for 2017 in
this committee.

13:17.397 --> 13:21.901 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Wyden also
pressed Mnuchin
about reports that he initially
didn't reveal

13:22.001 --> 13:27.640 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
more than $100 million of assets
on disclosure
forms and that he left out his
role directing

13:27.740 --> 13:28.675 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
some offshore accounts.

13:28.775 --> 13:29.976 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

13:30.076 --> 13:31.544 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RON WYDEN: How many employees
did you have
in Anguilla?

13:31.644 --> 13:33.479 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STEVEN MNUCHIN: We didn't have
any employees
in Anguilla.

13:33.579 --> 13:34.681 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

13:34.781 --> 13:36.215 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RON WYDEN: How many customers
did you have
there?

13:36.315 --> 13:38.918 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STEVEN MNUCHIN: We didn't have
any customers
that resided in Anguilla.

13:39.018 --> 13:39.919 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

13:40.019 --> 13:41.154 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
RON WYDEN: Did you have an
office there?

13:41.254 --> 13:43.956 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STEVEN MNUCHIN: We didn't have a
office ourselves
there.

13:44.057 --> 13:44.957 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

13:45.058 --> 13:46.793 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
RON WYDEN: So you just had a
post office box?

13:46.893 --> 13:50.296 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
STEVEN MNUCHIN: I would
diligently look at
these things, and I can assure
you I paid

13:50.396 --> 13:53.032 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
all my taxes as was required.

13:53.132 --> 13:55.401 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: New Jersey
Senator Bob Menendez
dug in.

13:55.501 --> 13:57.270 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

13:57.370 --> 13:59.939 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ROBERT MENENDEZ (D), New Jersey:
One doesn't
go and create offshore entities
at the end

14:00.039 --> 14:06.646 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of the day, other than to avoid,
in some form
or fashion, the tax laws of the
United States.

14:06.746 --> 14:08.548 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's pretty simple.

14:08.648 --> 14:12.385 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But Mnuchin
surprised some,
saying that he agrees that
offshore accounts

14:12.485 --> 14:14.387 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
are a problem he wants to fix.

14:14.487 --> 14:17.557 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVEN MNUCHIN: Well, first of
all, I'm absolutely
committed to work with you and
your office,

14:17.657 --> 14:23.696 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
as I have said, on tax
simplification and
to cut down and make sure that
we don't let

14:23.796 --> 14:25.698 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
anybody avoid taxes.

14:25.798 --> 14:29.335 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I would be happy to work with
your office
to simplify the tax code.

14:29.435 --> 14:33.039 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Committee
Chairman Orrin
Hatch called Democrats' focus on
those offshore

14:33.139 --> 14:34.941 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
accounts hypocritical and
ironic.

14:35.041 --> 14:36.209 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

14:36.309 --> 14:38.044 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
ORRIN HATCH (R), Utah:
Evidently, memories
are short.

14:38.144 --> 14:45.284 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
At least two of President
Obama's nominees
who now sit in his Cabinet had
Cayman Island

14:45.384 --> 14:47.019 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
holdings.

14:47.120 --> 14:51.190 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Democrats
returned to Mnuchin's
role with OneWest back in 2009.

14:51.290 --> 14:56.929 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
According to an independent
California housing
organization, OneWest
aggressively foreclosed

14:57.029 --> 15:00.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on some 60,000 homes while
Mnuchin ran it.

15:00.767 --> 15:05.404 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also this fall, two advocacy
groups asked
the Department of Housing and
Urban Development

15:05.505 --> 15:11.310 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
to investigate possible
discrimination, charging
that OneWest offered fewer
mortgages and options

15:11.410 --> 15:13.279 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to minorities.

15:13.379 --> 15:20.052 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mnuchin sold that bank for $3.4
billion in
2015 and has denied anything
improper.

15:20.153 --> 15:24.357 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He told the committee it wasn't
just about
profit, but saving a dying bank.

15:24.457 --> 15:29.695 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVEN MNUCHIN: Overall, I
helped many homeowners
stay in their homes and escape
financial ruin

15:29.796 --> 15:32.465 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
through my management of OneWest
Bank.

15:32.565 --> 15:40.940 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
My experience confirms that we
must identify
and eliminate unwise and
burdensome policies

15:41.040 --> 15:46.813 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
which contributed to the
disastrous outcomes
that came in the wake of the
financial collapse.

15:46.913 --> 15:51.751 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: At one point,
the treasury
nominee also pushed back at
Democrats.

15:51.851 --> 15:55.488 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVEN MNUCHIN: It seems to me,
in all due
respect, you just want to shoot
questions

15:55.588 --> 15:56.689 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
at me and not let you...

15:56.789 --> 15:57.924 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

15:58.024 --> 15:58.691 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SHERROD BROWN: I will let you
explain when
I'm done.

15:58.791 --> 16:00.326 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

16:00.426 --> 16:02.595 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STEVEN MNUCHIN: Let people at
least understand
these are complicated questions.

16:02.695 --> 16:03.596 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

16:03.696 --> 16:05.398 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
SHERROD BROWN: They are
complicated.

16:05.498 --> 16:08.201 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: As the top
economic official,
there was plenty of policy talk,
too.

16:08.301 --> 16:12.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mnuchin said he would enforce
current Russian
sanctions and would keep the
Consumer Financial

16:12.872 --> 16:16.142 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Protection Bureau, though he
questioned its
funding source.

16:16.242 --> 16:18.144 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And Lisa joins me
now.

16:18.244 --> 16:20.146 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, Lisa, you were there for the
hours of
this hearing.

16:20.246 --> 16:23.082 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Did you come away with a
particular impression
of Steven Mnuchin?

16:23.182 --> 16:25.151 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: As you saw, I
had a good
seat.

16:25.251 --> 16:29.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I have to say, I think what
he was trying
to telegraph to the committee
that he is more

16:29.188 --> 16:31.624 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
moderate than his opponents are
casting him.

16:31.724 --> 16:36.963 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, we have to see what he does
if he's confirmed
as secretary, but things like
the CFPB, saying

16:37.063 --> 16:40.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that he would keep that, and he
also said
things like, I want to increase
the staff

16:40.333 --> 16:42.235 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
at the IRS.

16:42.335 --> 16:45.571 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
These are things conservatives
have traditionally
gone after, and he's said to
this committee,

16:45.671 --> 16:47.106 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I'm going to be more reasonable.

16:47.206 --> 16:48.608 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He used those words.

16:48.708 --> 16:50.943 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: CFPB being the
Consumer Financial
Protection Bureau.

16:51.043 --> 16:52.778 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Financial
Protection Bureau.

16:52.879 --> 16:54.947 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: I want to ask you
about the
status of one of the
president-elect's other

16:55.047 --> 16:59.819 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
nominees to be the budget
director, Mick Mulvaney,
the congressman from South
Carolina.

16:59.919 --> 17:03.289 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He has run into some problems
over an employee
of his family.

17:03.389 --> 17:04.557 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: That's correct.

17:04.657 --> 17:06.225 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
That's right.

17:06.325 --> 17:09.962 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He told the Senate about a month
ago that
he found out a caregiver for his
children

17:10.062 --> 17:13.165 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who worked for him for a few
years, he didn't
pay taxes for that person.

17:13.266 --> 17:17.737 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he's now paying those back
taxes, but
it seems that this might really
be a problem.

17:17.837 --> 17:22.174 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the reason I think so is
that we haven't
seen statements from leading
Republicans supporting

17:22.275 --> 17:23.943 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
him today.

17:24.043 --> 17:27.079 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And I spoke to another
Republican senator,
Judy, who says there's another
issue.

17:27.179 --> 17:31.918 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
They're concerned because
Mulvaney in the
past has asked to cut defense
spending in

17:32.018 --> 17:33.519 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a way that Republicans don't
like.

17:33.619 --> 17:35.688 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, it will come down to his
hearing next
week.

17:35.788 --> 17:37.857 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All right, now,
one other thing
I want to ask you about.

17:37.957 --> 17:43.329 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We know that Republicans want as
many of these
nominees confirmed as soon as
possible.

17:43.429 --> 17:47.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Democrats are not in the
majority, but they
have the ability to slow them
down, and that's

17:47.133 --> 17:48.668 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
what they're doing.

17:48.768 --> 17:50.469 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: You heard that
from Chuck
Schumer in John's report
earlier.

17:50.569 --> 17:52.505 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
That's right.

17:52.605 --> 17:56.375 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Democrats said today they are
going to allow
two nominees to be confirmed
tomorrow on Inauguration

17:56.475 --> 17:57.376 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Day.

17:57.476 --> 17:58.377 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Just two?

17:58.477 --> 18:00.413 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Just two, in
the evening.

18:00.513 --> 18:03.849 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Those are the defense secretary,
James Mattis,
and also Department of Homeland
Security Secretary

18:03.950 --> 18:06.052 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
John -- I'm sorry -- John Kelly.

18:06.152 --> 18:12.191 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The two Marine Corps generals
are going to
be confirmed, but not
necessarily Mike Pompeo.

18:12.291 --> 18:16.395 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Senator Ron Wyden has an
objection to the
CIA director-designate.

18:16.495 --> 18:17.863 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That's a real concern for
Republicans.

18:17.964 --> 18:19.498 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They say that's a security risk.

18:19.598 --> 18:21.767 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It might be a political risk for
Democrats.

18:21.867 --> 18:27.340 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They say Pompeo is likely to be
confirmed
soon, but it doesn't look like
tomorrow.

18:27.440 --> 18:32.111 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
As for the rest of these
nominees, Democrats
say they are planning to slow
down the process,

18:32.211 --> 18:33.512 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
that they want more
deliberation.

18:33.612 --> 18:35.481 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
How can they do that if they're
in the minority?

18:35.581 --> 18:41.120 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, under Senate rules, they
can use procedure
to add lots of debate time for
each nominee.

18:41.220 --> 18:43.923 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It looks like they're planning
to do that.

18:44.023 --> 18:47.059 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Watch the especially
non-controversial ones
like Elaine Chao, Ben Carson.

18:47.159 --> 18:48.327 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What happens with them?

18:48.427 --> 18:49.662 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And Republicans
not happy about
this.

18:49.762 --> 18:51.630 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: No, they're not
happy.

18:51.731 --> 18:55.968 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's building to not just a
sense of typical
strategy here, but real tension
between the

18:56.068 --> 18:56.969 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
two sides.

18:57.069 --> 18:59.171 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Lisa Desjardins,
thank you.

18:59.271 --> 19:01.007 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Appreciate it.

19:01.107 --> 19:04.610 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The other confirmation hearing
we were watching
today was the one for Mr.
Trump's pick for

19:04.710 --> 19:08.447 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the secretary of energy, former
Texas Governor
Rick Perry.

19:08.547 --> 19:12.852 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Now, Perry called for the
elimination of that
very department when he ran for
president

19:12.952 --> 19:14.720 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
in 2012.

19:14.820 --> 19:17.623 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then he forgot the name of
the department
during a debate.

19:17.723 --> 19:23.062 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, much of the department's
role is devoted
to monitoring, maintaining and
keeping safe

19:23.162 --> 19:24.964 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
