Energy do not
reflect my current thinking.

19:41.080 --> 19:46.619 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In fact, after being briefed on
so many of
the vital functions of the
Department of Energy,

19:46.719 --> 19:50.256 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I regret recommending its
elimination.

19:50.356 --> 19:55.461 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Perry, who has
previously has
denied the science of climate
change, also

19:55.561 --> 19:57.863 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
spoke about his views on that
subject.

19:57.963 --> 20:02.268 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Senators pressed him on whether
he would even
protect scientists within the
department and

20:02.368 --> 20:04.170 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
their budget.

20:04.270 --> 20:07.473 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And along a similar line of
questioning, he
also was asked about reports
that the Trump

20:07.573 --> 20:13.112 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
transition team wants to cut
funding for programs
promoting renewable energy.

20:13.212 --> 20:14.847 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Here's how some of that played
out.

20:14.947 --> 20:18.117 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
RICK PERRY: I believe that
climate is changing.

20:18.217 --> 20:23.589 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I believe some of it is
naturally occurring,
but some of it is caused by
manmade activity.

20:23.689 --> 20:32.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The question is how we address
it in a thoughtful
way that doesn't compromise
economic growth,

20:32.798 --> 20:36.335 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it affects the affordability of
energy or
American jobs.

20:36.435 --> 20:38.304 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

20:38.404 --> 20:43.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARIA CANTWELL (D), Washington:
Do you plan
to protect the science research
at DOE related

20:43.175 --> 20:44.944 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to climate?

20:45.044 --> 20:49.215 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RICK PERRY: Senator, I am going
to protect
the men and women of the
scientific community

20:49.315 --> 20:55.454 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from anyone that would attack
them no matter
what their reason may be, at the
Department

20:55.554 --> 20:56.455 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of Energy.

20:56.555 --> 20:57.756 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

20:57.857 --> 20:59.558 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DEBBIE STABENOW (D), Michigan:
How do you
see your role?

20:59.658 --> 21:03.629 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
You're coming into a new
position where we
are talking about massive cuts
in the kinds

21:03.729 --> 21:11.036 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
of things that you have
advocated for, you
supported in your role as
governor things,

21:11.137 --> 21:17.877 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
